description: Angel Brimstone and demon Fire are still trying to make good on their "little mistake" from 5,000 years ago, rounding up all the devils and fallen angels they set free! Someone's about had enough of their antics, though, because they're about to go out of the frying pan and into the Forge! The former blacksmith to the gods, The Forge is now an invincible freelance assassin, and he's been hired to take out the delectable duo! Can they stand the heat?

Elizabeth Morgan has been on the run from a serial killer for the past two years. Under the protection of the police, relocated to to await the killer's apprehension. But after the murder of a young girl and her parents on the outskirts of , must once again leave everything behind and seek safety in a new life!

Part 2 of the enthralling PINOCCHIO collection is here! This is the MUST-READ conclusion to the terrifying story of the wooden puppet who longed to by a real boy. Gepetto attempts to rescue his son who refuses to give up on. But a vicious evil stirs inside of Pinnochio and it might be too late for Gepetto to help him. Can a fatherâ€™s love prove to be enough to save the wooden boy or will evil prevail and doom Gepetto once and for all?

As the story picks up, the father asks what his son has done, but when he doesn't answer he allows him to go to school by himself so that he can stay at home and read some more of the fairy tale. After killing the two thieves Pinocchio was dragged into the water, and his father goes in after him. The two are then swallowed by a whale. Gepetto makes a deal with Pinocchio, allowing him to go free provided he try to reform, while he must stay in the whale's stomach. A fairy comes to rescue him and tells him he must be there for Pinocchio. He escapes and when he finds Pinocchio he finds he has killed more, and then Pinocchio kills him as well. The fairy then shows up and reveals she had intended this all along. When the father in the real world finishes reading this he finds his son has set his school on fire. He runs in to rescue him but chooses to leave him to die and rescues another girl instead. Belinda drives away with the boy (now transformed into a wooden person) alongside her.

description: The Sopranos was about the soap opera of upper-class mob life. What do you get, Gary asked, when you transplant that tension to the African-American gangs of inner-city Los Angeles? Answer -You get the story of CQ, a young man who's set his sights on becoming the boss of the L.A. rackets -if he lives to see the dawn! A potent mix of American Gangster and The Wire for fans of Brubaker's Criminal!

Based on skill alone, Renee Tempete should be the new Galaxy Girl. Instead, a buxom blonde with no actual powers holds the title. As events unfold, Renee struggles not only against monsters, criminals and giant robots, but also a society that desperately wants to keep her in her place.

As dissension is revealed within the Templar priesthood, Lord Wotan makes a powerful public declaration regarding Karic's destiny, and Cassius is entrusted with a secret mission and a sacred task he no longer believes in.
name: The Prophecy, Part 6: The Symbol

description:
Null and Void conflict with one another and Superman tries to escape a strange void. Meanwhile, Batman finds himself caught in the struggle between the Swedes and the Russians, who are vying for the frozen Swordfish and Barracuda.

  1. Cover by Ed Hannigan and Klaus Janson.
  2. "Part 2 Lost in the Void" written by David Anthony Kraft, penciled by Trevor Von Eeden, inked by Pablo Marcos, colored by Carl Gafford and lettered by Bob Lappan.

As Mr. Null and Mr. Void taunt the Dark Knight, Superman tries to find a way out of the nightmare land he's trapped in!
name: Part 2 Lost in the Void

description: " The story of Mother Grimm concludes, as Batman confronts the villainous Cyanide. Meanwhile, Robin stands alone against Mother Grimm's hoard of loyal followers"--DC solicitation.
name: Grimm Part 5 of 5: I Prove My Worth

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: The first issue of this four-part mini-series kicks off during the events that occurred during Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles Volume Four #5, specifically the time period immediately following the arrival of the Utrom's 'Moon Island' on Earth. Michelangelo is swept up in the tension and chaos that grips New York in the wake of humanity's first contact with alien life!

The acclaimed dinosaur fantasy epic continues as the occupying Talpid force attempts to squelch the Monanti slave uprising by killing their leaders and banishing the King. Meanwhile, Lilli uses ancient knowledge to raise a reptilian army for an all-out assault on the city that banished her.
name: Penalty for Treason

description: This is it! The explosive, action-packed grand finale to the hit series! Not only will Bluewater reveal the winners of the 'New Pistolfist Costume Design Contest,' but - spoiler alert! - Ben Franklin dies in this issue!

In issue one, written by series writer Ben Gruber, the original Speed Racer has disappeared! Also, he had some babies. Speed Racer: The Next Generation follows his sons as they learn the fine art of racing at Spritle's Racing Academy and discover the designs for the Mach 6. With its gasless engine, the Mach 6 is so cool, it's one number better than the Mach 5 (which is still pretty awesome)! Together with their friends, Speed (Jr.) and X try to solve the mysterious disappearance of their father, complete the Mach 6 and stick it to the evil forces of big oil bent on their destruction.

The Omega Team comes to Bucharest, hot on the trail of the insidious witch Lilith and her vampire consort. In a blazing display of bullet-riddled action, the team must fight their way through ugly vampires, golems and even owl mutants in order to claim victory!

Creator Lora Innes writes and illustrates the tale of 17-year-old Beatrice "Bea" Whaley, a student who begins having vivid dreams about a brave and handsome soldier named Alan Warrenâ€¦ a member of an elite group known as Knowltonâ€™s Rangers that fought during the Revolutionary War. Prone to keeping her head in the clouds, Bea welcomes her nightly adventures in 1776; filled with danger and romance they give her much to muse about the next day. But it is not long before Beatrice questions whether her dreams are simply dreams or something moreâ€¦
name: Act One: The Consequence Of Nathan Hale

description: The Lesbian Pirates have been captured! Stuck in a holding cell on Male Man's ship, it's up to Susie to save the day. But when given the chance, will she take a free ride back to Earth?

volume.name: I Was Kidnapped By Lesbian Pirates From Outer Space

description: Teamed with new Bugle reporter, Billy Walters, Peter finds himself interviewing witnesses to a battle between the nefarious DOCTOR OCTOPUS and the amazing SPIDER-MAN, and discovers that every story has many sides...and not everyone is a Spider-fan!
name: Pieces Of The Puzzle

description: Alliances, friendships and faith are all tested as the 5th Squadron come face to face with the perils of The Source. In their relentless search for a missing member, the squadron encounters a place outside of their collective understanding that is considerably more than it seems! However, there is one being who might help, but finding him means avoiding the giant creatures, the Elementals! But the Elementals are are everywhere - in the air, under the ground, in the water - and not even Britain's elite flying team and Germany's top ace can imagine the consequences of getting home!
name: Chapter Two: Water

volume.name: Ray Harryhausen Presents: War Of The Elementals

description: The wars of unification have ended and Rome is stronger than ever. Was it enough to change the future and push humanity to new heights? Find out in the epic conclusion of PAX ROMANA.
name: The Great Society

description: After escaping from Narimar against all odds, Blythe's boss at Clearfleet Airlines takes her to a high-stakes business summit in Mexico City. She discovers the corporation out to buy Clearfleet has a secret agenda â€“ one that involves an old enemy and the feathered serpent she's been seeing in her dreams.
name: Masks and Other Memories

description: Search for the truth inside this new miniseries based on the hit FOX television show! A research scientist, recently agitated by paranoid fears, is found dead in his suburban D.C. apartment. His sister refuses to accept the coroner's ruling that his death was suicide from a self-inflicted gunshot wound. Federal investigator Scully discovers forensic details that would seem to defy rational explanation and when her partner Agent Mulder learns the scientist was working on a top-secret project for a government contractor, Mulder becomes agitated by his own paranoid fears, which eerily parallels the behavior that led to the scientist's death!

Private lives and public expectations are tearing the Mates apart. Crusader reveals a hip, '70s-style island HQ in hopes of keeping the heroes together. But it's a call from space that rallies the team. Back in the present day, Nick and Ethel discover a 35-year-old secret hidden among the lunch boxes and action figures of the world's biggest collection of Mates memorabilia.
name: With a Little Help From my Friends

description: John Constantine's journey of self-discovery comes full circle as he returns to the Ravenscar mental hospital he spent years at to face down the individual who has been manipulating him from the shadows. But this rogue has been hiding in the last place Constantine would ever think to look.
name: The Roots Of Coincidence, Part 3

description: The Thing can't stay out of trouble, but at least he makes friends wherever he goes! The Ever-Lovin' Idol o' Millions teams up with heroes both frontline and forgotten against menaces spanning time and space! Gods! Aliens! Spies! Demons! Dinosaurs! Time travellers! Martial artists! The Living Eraser and the Mountain That Walked Like a Man! A veritable who's who of history's horror heroes! Collects Marvel Feature #11-12; Marvel Two-In-One #1-20, 22-25 and Annual #1; Fantastic Four Annual #11; and Marvel Team-Up #47.
name: Volume 1

description: THERE'S A TIGRA ON THE LOOSE!: The Griffin is on a rampage, and it's up to the Avengers to stop him! But why is Tigra secretly observing the fight from afar, and why has she been spying on the Avengers for days? And who, in turn, has been spying on HER? Plus, a new Avenger joins the ranks!
name: The Lady & The Tigra

description: To celebrate his 40th Anniversary, the mini man of might finally gets his due! Ant-Man leaps into bold black-and-white action as we reprint all of his TALES TO ASTONISH appearances (that's TTA #27 as well as #35 - #69, kids!) in one giant volume! Witness Hank Pym's transformation into Giant-Man and his blossoming relationship with the winsome Wasp! Stan Lee and Jack Kirby's smallest creation is still one of their finest!
name: Volume 1
Masquerade

description: Premiere issue in a series of educational comic books designed to promote awareness of various issues of concern to society, with profits being donated to related charitable organizations.
name: Assault on Campus

description: When Army aviator Mike Aragon's helicopter crashes into the Pacific, he is lost at sea and presumed dead. When he's found a week later, in perfect health, washed up on Oahu's North Shore, he has no idea where he's been. As he regains his memory, he begins to believe that his rescuers may have been aliens, poised to pass judgment on mankind. Follow Mike as he risks his marriage and his career to find out if he's right... and more importantly, if he can stop them. A story of aliens, heroism, and humanity, set in beautiful Hawaii. Includes a bonus 5-page preview of the next After Hours series, J.A.A.T. (Joint Armored Attack Team), by Darren Sanchez and Dennis Calero.

name: Godwalking

description: Twenty years after the genetic program that created them was brought to an end, Nikken's half human creations struggle for survival and acceptance in the world of man.

Immortal muscleman, The Grand! Super-patriot, Justice Hall! The tragic Jeckyll-and-Hyde-in-one-horrific-body known as Schaff! Kastra: sexy teen daughter of an alien space commander! Together they are their world's greatest heroes. But when they're accidentally transported to our Earth, a place where superheroes are merely comic book characters, their heroism, morality and ethics are out the window on a planet they can rule! Superhero archetypes are skewered and comic book industry factions satirized in this four-color punch-'em-up by publishing mogul Larry Young and Switchblade Honey artist, Brandon McKinney!
Read Bill Clinton's story, then flip it over to read Gennifer Flowers story.
name: The Bill Clinton Story

Fan-favorite artist Tim Sale, best known for Batman: The Long Halloween and Spider-Man: Blue, talks extensively about his career from his early Grey Archer Press illustrations to his recent work on Hulk: Gray. Beautifully illustrated with pencil sketches and finished pieces throughout, this book is a must for Tim Sale afficianados.

description: The adventures of the disbanded TEEN TITANS continue! As a favor to his old principal, Mack Harlin, the Kid goes undercover in a Denver high school to track down someone who broke into NORAD. But being a mild-mannered student may be more than Superboy can handle, especially when his target turns out to be the Titans' Risk. ...
